{{SupportPage|vendor=Belkin|vs_id_old=372}} [http://www.seattlewireless.net/Belkin_F5D7230-4 F5D7230-4 series on SeattleWireless] [http://www.linux-hacker.net/misc/F5D7230/ Images and info on linux-hacker.net] The device is an [[Askey RT210W]]. The FCC ID printed on the v1000 unit may be QDS-BRCM1005. The FCC ID of the parent model is H8N-RT210W. "3028-000192" is silkscreened on the main board. "3017-001200" is silkscreened on the wireless module The FCC ID printed on later revision v1 models is probably K7SF5D7230-4 (or misprinted as K7SF5D72304). Other sources say this model uses BCM4712.
